Introduction

Task 3 focuses on exploring programming platforms and collaborative tools that support learning, problem-solving, and teamwork in a digital environment.
 Programming Platforms

Programming platforms such as HackerRank, CodeChef, and HackerEarth help students improve coding skills by solving problems of varying difficulty levels. These platforms enhance logical thinking, algorithmic skills, and programming knowledge through regular practice.

 Collaborative Learning Tools

Collaborative tools like Google Forms, Google Docs, and Google Drive enable students to work together, share files, collect responses, and manage data efficiently. These tools support teamwork and communication in academic activities.

 Objectives of Task
To understand coding platforms
To develop problem-solving skills
To learn collaboration using digital tools
To collect and analyze data using online forms
Learning Outcome

This task helped in improving coding ability, understanding digital collaboration, and using online tools effectively for academic purposes. It also enhanced teamwork and data management skills.
